# Svelte markup: no `motion.*` tags

This project uses **Svelte**, not React/Framer Motion. Never emit markup like `<motion.div>`, `<motion.span>`, or any other `motion.*` element — not even briefly in a patch. Use Bulma `notification`, `box`, or plain HTML elements for layout.

Use normal HTML elements instead:

```svelte
<!-- BAD -->
<motion.div class="column">...</motion.div>

<!-- GOOD -->
<div class="column">...</div>
```

Legitimate uses of the word "motion" in this codebase are unrelated (e.g. `import { tweened } from "svelte/motion"`, `motionLine` data fields). Do not confuse those with JSX-style `motion` component tags.

## Enforcement

`npm run lint:markup` scans `src/**/*.svelte` and fails on `<motion.*>` or `</motion.*>`. It runs as part of `npm run check`. After editing any `.svelte` file, run `npm run lint:markup` before finishing.
